## ğŸ¯ Key Capabilities

### Multiple Input Methods
1. **Manual Entry** - Type credentials directly
2. **Environment Variables** - Auto-load from .env
3. **JSON Upload** - Upload Firebase config file
4. **JSON Export** - Download for backup

### Supported Credentials
- Project ID (required)
- API Key (required)
- Auth Domain (required)
- Database URL (optional)
- Storage Bucket (optional)
- Messaging Sender ID (optional)
- App ID (optional)
- Measurement ID (optional)

### Validation
- Project ID format (lowercase, hyphens)
- API Key length (minimum 20 chars)
- Auth Domain format (.firebaseapp.com)
- Storage Bucket format (.appspot.com)
- Real-time error detection
- User-friendly error messages

### Security Features
- Password field protection (show/hide)
- Input validation before saving
- Confirmation dialogs
- Secure backup/restore
- No credentials in console logs

