## ğŸ” Security Best Practices

### Environment Setup
```env
# Create .env.local file with Firebase credentials
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSy...
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=yourapp.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=https://yourapp.firebaseio.com
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=yourapp.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=123456789
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:123456789:web:abc...
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX
```

### File Security
- Never commit .env to version control
- Use .gitignore for environment files
- Store JSON exports securely
- Rotate API keys periodically
- Limit access to admin users

### Credential Protection
- API keys shown as password field
- Toggle eye icon to show/hide
- No credentials logged to console
- Safe backup/restore process

